ogin=gwarith>Gwarith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/12/02 11:25:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 3 points to spend in Realm Abilities.  Which one?</span><hr size=1> I got three points to spend in Realm Abilities.  I want to get one of the big 3-point costing ability <p>Gwarith FoeHammer<BR>2x Troll Skald<BR>Iseult<BR><BR>The Kool-Aid Skald<BR>"OHHH YEAH!!!!!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elerinn>Elerinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/12/02 2:15:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I like Mystic Crystal Lore I</span><hr size=1> You can't beat getting 30% of your power back every 5 minutes.. Best 3 points I have spend on realm abilities. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blackielawless>Blackie Lawless</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/12/02 3:25:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What do YOU think?</span><hr size=1> MCL is very nice.  The only reason I got it is because I did NOT put any points into Charisma when I started out (had no idea what I was doing), and I solo a lot so I tend to run out of power often.  If that doesn't happen to you, or if you tend to have a healer around to drop a purity on ya, you might want to pass MCL up.<br><br>I would prolly look at what bugs you most about your skald and try and find a RA that maybe counteracts it or tries to lessen it's effects.  If you have end problems (like I do), maybe go for tireless 1 and maybe augmented con 1 (you need aug con 3 to get second wind which fully recharges your end.  Not something I'm shooting for, but to each his own <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )leaving you with 1 point.  Maybe put those points into first aid 1 to get you that much closer to Ignore Pain.  Just look through the RA's and see what makes the most sense for you.  Prolly not the most helpful info, but... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Personally I have the following atm:<br><br>MCL 1<br>Purge<br>Tireless 1 (I hear tireless 3 is awesome)<br>Avoidance of Magic 1 (no idea why, it was late, it sounded good at the time... still might be good, who knows)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gladton>Gladton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/15/02 5:17:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3 points to spend in Realm Abilities.  Which one?</span><hr size=1> Save it.<br><br>Buy First Aid and after that Ignore Pain.<br><br>After that buy Purge.<br><br>After that, the next choice should be clear because by then you are fairly experienced with RvR. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ujaliawolfsdottir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalia Wolfsdottir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/15/02 10:55:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3 points to spend in Realm Abilities.  Which one?</span><hr size=1> Don't waste any points on First Aid. They said they were going to make it a 30% non-combat heal, but they never did. It currently heals about 85-100 hitpoints. That's it. Furthermore, it's no longer a requirement for Ignore Pain (or at least it's not supposed to be).<br><br>Go with Mystic Crystal Lore. It's by far the most helpful Realm Ability for the points it costs. <p><img src="http://users.rcn.com/jmaclear/rilee_sig.gif" height=170 width=408 alt="Rilee MacLear"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uevldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/15/02 1:06:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3 points to spend in Realm Abilities.  Which one?</span><hr size=1> er actually first aid i