h one?</span><hr size=1> It IS fixed? When did that happen? I guess I stopped using it after It wasn't getting fixed. Did I just miss the patch announcement?<br><br>Anyway, I think I'm going to stand behind my assertion that MCL is the better deal for the investment it requires. <p><img src="http://users.rcn.com/jmaclear/rilee_sig.gif" height=170 width=408 alt="Rilee MacLear"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gladton>Gladton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/18/02 2:10:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3 points to spend in Realm Abilities.  Which one?</span><hr size=1> yes, it is fixed.<br><br>but it doesn't really matter...Ignore Pain itself is so powerful compared to the other RA's. New and improved First Aid is just top of the cake.<br><br>I have 1400hp...let's say I hit the IP button at 1300hp...that means I have effectively 2700hp now, in a fight I could also put down my sword for 2 seconds and hit the First Aid button and heal an additional 840 hitpoints.<br><br>You buy your MCL which will only help you before or after a fight, rarely during. But the smart persons go straight for the 3540 hitpoints solution.<br><br>But, I guess it will be nerfed when a smart Hero who put +10 con at start, maxxed con through items and buffs and with stag form can abuse the percentages so much it's not even funny anymore.<br><br>Let's just play with the thought....<br><br>hero, 1600hp?<br>buffs...another 400? a total of 2000 then.<br>Stag form, add 50% to that.<br><br>3000 hp.<br><br>Ignore Pain, another 3000 hp<br>First Aid, another 1800...<br><br>7800 hp. waow. A full group of mages will run out of power before they beat down that meatwall. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/urobertoffob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robert of FoB</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://imagehost.auctionwatch.com/preview/uo/uo4real/robFOB.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/18/02 8:38:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://imagehost.auctionwatch.com/bin/imageserver.x/00000000/trapmasta/robfob5.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3 points to spend in Realm Abilities.  Which one?</span><hr size=1> who goes after the meatshields first? mezz them run past right after a bard/caster.<br><br>that just how I would rvr =p <p><center><HTML><BODY><img src="http://brightblade.uols.net/robert.gif"<center><BR><BR><center><img src="http://brightblade.uols.net/banner.gif"<center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=230.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=230.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=230.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This